<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/211</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-15T16:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 16, 12.31
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8678. War Trade Board from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>:</p>
                            <p>No. 165. Swedish delegates have received word from Swedish Government
                                saying it considers itself not bound by <hi rend="italic">modus
                                    vivendi</hi> owing to your new bunkering rules<note n="1" xml:id="d314fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>. <ref target="#pg_946">p.
                                    946</ref>.</note> of which neither the Swedish delegates here,
                                nor any Allied representatives, had any intimation. The <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> contained the only bunkering
                                arrangements and control of boats that the Swedes are willing to
                                accept, and the Allied position was considered adequately
                                safeguarded by the terms of the <hi rend="italic">modus
                                vivendi</hi>. It is most urgent to have matter settled on account of
                                desire of Swedes to get commodities released, especially phosphate
                                rock in time to be of use for crops, and desire of Allies to use <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> ships. Are you not willing make
                                a declaration that your bunkering rules do not apply to <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi?</hi> Understand British and French
                                are cabling their Washington Embassy. The matter is urgent so please
                                give this immediate attention.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>